x:Snow is white
y:Schnee ist weiss

x and y are identical propositions

P and Q are the same proposition if and only if
 for any person S and any propositional attitude A
  S has A towards P if and only if S has A towards Q
  
P and Q are the same proposition if and only if 
  for any person S any propositional attitude
    they have towards P, they have toward Q
    
A: six is even and seven is odd
B: seven is odd and six is even
